![image](data:image/png;base64,)


## What is an Observation?


Observations are the heart of CoMapeo. They allow you to capture data about what you see in the field, including text, photos, audios, and location.


---


## Create a New Observation


### 🟢 Try it


> ### 👣 Steps  
>   
> **Step 1** From the <img src="/comapeo-docs/images/emojis/icon-map_c21704e3f6c4e1d9_32850869.jpg" alt="icon-map-low" className="emoji" style={{display: "inline", height: "1.2em", width: "auto", verticalAlign: "text-bottom", margin: "0 0.1em"}} /> map view, tap the <img src="/comapeo-docs/images/emojis/icon-capture_9c1ea5db8f0a2d02_32850797.jpg" alt="comapeo-capture-low" className="emoji" style={{display: "inline", height: "1.2em", width: "auto", verticalAlign: "text-bottom", margin: "0 0.1em"}} /> capture(/orange?) button to create a new Observation.  
>   
> ---  
>   
> **Step 2** Choose the appropriate category for the Observation you are mapping.  
>   
> ---  
>   
> **Step 3** Add a description, details, <img src="/comapeo-docs/images/emojis/icon-add-photo_be966fefc62a2f69_32850966.jpg" alt="comapeo-add-photo-low" className="emoji" style={{display: "inline", height: "1.2em", width: "auto", verticalAlign: "text-bottom", margin: "0 0.1em"}} /> photos, and <img src="/comapeo-docs/images/emojis/icon-add-audio_64fdb41aa5ff26ba_32851050.jpg" alt="icon-add-audio-low" className="emoji" style={{display: "inline", height: "1.2em", width: "auto", verticalAlign: "text-bottom", margin: "0 0.1em"}} /> audios as needed. (Described in detail below)  
>   
> ---  
>   
> **Step 4** Save your Observation. It will appear on your map and in the Observation list.


> ### 👣 Step by step  
>   
> 1. From either Map view or Camera view, tap on the <img src="/comapeo-docs/images/emojis/icon-capture_9c1ea5db8f0a2d02_32850797.jpg" alt="comapeo-capture-low" className="emoji" style={{display: "inline", height: "1.2em", width: "auto", verticalAlign: "text-bottom", margin: "0 0.1em"}} /> large orange button with the plus symbol.  
>   
> 2. Choose a category  
>   
> 3. The editor will appear and you can add notes to your observation. You can add details, photos, and/or audio if desired. The instructions for those are below.  
>   
> 4. When ready, tap on the blue check in the upper right to Save your observation.
